1
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:48,320
{\an8}<i>With a pretty face and figure like yours,</i>

2
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:51,120
{\an8}<i>you'd be better at something fun.</i>

3
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:55,600
{\an8}Please me properly, and I'll promote you.

4
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:59,000
{\an8}<i>Everything about Taiga, report only to me.</i>

5
00:02:59,080 --> 00:02:59,920
{\an8}Yes, sir.

6
00:03:10,160 --> 00:03:11,240
Come here.

7
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:18,800
I want some new designs
for the next collection.

8
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,680
You draw really well.

9
00:03:23,640 --> 00:03:24,560
Want to try?

10
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:27,320
I can't draw.

11
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:38,480
Stand still while you draw here,
so the wound doesn't tear.

12
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:48,880
There's no right or wrong in art.

13
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:53,440
Beauty comes from the heart, not the eyes.

14
00:03:55,280 --> 00:03:56,680
I don't get it.

15
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:04,000
Use your heart. Use your feelings.

16
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:06,640
That's all you need.

17
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:42,920
I took my medicine, and I'm sleepy.
I think I'll go lie down.

18
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:53,600
Taiga, Madam Ratee
is in front of your house.

19
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:25,600
Where have you been?
I've missed you so much.

20
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:38,040
Since when did you start resenting me?

21
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:45,040
I could never resent someone
who once risked her life to save mine.

22
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:51,080
Stop talking about debts of gratitude.

23
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:56,520
Our relationship is only about love

24
00:05:57,520 --> 00:05:58,760
and marriage.

25
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:03,640
Please, Ratee.

26
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:07,040
Sometimes I have work, I have business.

27
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:15,200
You make it sound
like I'm invading your personal space.

28
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:22,720
I'm willing to be second.

29
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:26,320
Because your father
comes first in your heart.

30
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:32,800
But after him, it must be me.

31
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:37,200
You're not allowed to let
any other woman come between us.

32
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:42,040
I won't accept it.

33
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,560
You know that, Taiga?

34
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:30,600
Why are you pretending to sleep?

35
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:38,200
I'm not pretending.
I actually fell asleep.

36
00:07:40,520 --> 00:07:44,400
Go ahead and keep sleeping.
I can sit here and work.

37
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,440
I want to be alone.

38
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:23,320
Te, I'll go upstairs first.
There's a meeting.

39
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,799
- Sorry.
- Sorry.

40
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:06,360
Don't look!

41
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:16,480
My wound still hurts.
Why are you forcing me to draw?

42
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:22,000
If you want to know what's in my heart,

43
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:25,360
the distance between us is too far.

44
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:32,520
But the distance between us
shouldn't be this close.

45
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,360
STAFF ONLY

46
00:10:57,560 --> 00:10:59,440
Greeting me with a gun, Khanin?

47
00:11:02,560 --> 00:11:05,000
It's been a long time
since I saw my old boss.

48
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:08,720
The one who loves his team
more than anything.

49
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:11,160
You've got a new boss now.

50
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:13,840
Ever since I was pressured

51
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:17,400
and kicked out
of the police force, which I loved,

52
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,880
I promised myself

53
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:24,120
I'd never be anyone's subordinate again
until I've avenged everyone.

54
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:26,440
You're as determined as ever.

55
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:29,840
But nothing's the same anymore.

56
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:33,560
Right. Nothing is the same.

57
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:35,880
You survived,

58
00:11:36,640 --> 00:11:39,400
kept working, while the rest
of your subordinates died,

59
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:43,360
disappeared, lost their futures.

60
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:45,680
You survived alone, living comfortably!

61
00:11:45,760 --> 00:11:48,760
I have to fight for myself first.

62
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:50,280
For yourself.

63
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:56,120
It's a shame I ever had faith in you.

64
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:06,160
It's time

65
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:09,760
that you take responsibility
for everything, Punlop.

66
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,200
Damn it!

67
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:38,960
Your made-to-order meal.

68
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:41,720
Just how you like it.

69
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:46,440
You're good at a lot of things.

70
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:58,440
Pink mochi with pickled sakura leaves,
only available this season.

71
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:06,720
Food makes us feel like we're with family.

72
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:11,840
I'm alone. I don't have a family.

73
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:14,720
My dad died long ago.

74
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:08,600
Did I say something wrong?

75
00:14:11,640 --> 00:14:13,000
Because I mentioned my dad?

76
00:14:46,080 --> 00:14:47,320
I'm fine.

77
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:50,480
You should eat.

78
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:33,000
Any info yet?

79
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:39,280
Not yet. Rin's being careful. How's Ratee?

80
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:43,240
A mess, totally wasted.

81
00:15:43,320 --> 00:15:45,600
But don't worry. I'm watching her.

82
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:48,160
Thanks a lot.

83
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:52,120
Dhammatat, you went too hard on Rin.

84
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:58,200
It had to be that rough.
Only then can you get Rin.

85
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:03,280
Make every second count.
Being this close to her,

86
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:04,840
something's bound to slip.

87
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,200
Thank you.

88
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:02,600
Is everything done?

89
00:17:41,520 --> 00:17:44,760
You're as determined as ever.
But nothing's the same anymore.

90
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:47,720
It's a shame I ever had faith in you.

91
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:49,800
I have to fight for myself first.

92
00:17:59,240 --> 00:18:02,960
Is this the reward for dedication?

93
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:07,520
Right now,

94
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:12,560
the arrest team is under investigation,
accused of misconduct.

95
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:17,840
The media's criticizing us,
saying we overstepped our duties

96
00:18:18,520 --> 00:18:21,440
and abused our power against civilians.
They're not civilians!

97
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:24,800
They're human traffickers.

98
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:28,840
Backed by higher-ups
protecting the gang from the top.

99
00:18:33,880 --> 00:18:35,040
Sir.

100
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:37,920
Do we really have to be the scapegoats?

101
00:18:43,520 --> 00:18:45,440
I'll protect our team to the end.

102
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:48,560
Truth never dies.

103
00:18:52,480 --> 00:18:55,560
You have to fight, sir.
We won't abandon you.

104
00:18:56,480 --> 00:19:00,720
If we take them on, everyone will see
that you dared to challenge injustice.

105
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:05,840
We can uproot them.

106
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:11,600
Only if the higher-ups
give the green light

107
00:19:13,080 --> 00:19:16,120
and ignore the bribes
those scoundrels throw at them.

108
00:19:26,160 --> 00:19:27,680
Let's fight together, Khanin.

109
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:30,440
Yes.

110
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:43,560
Can't you drop this case, son?

111
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:46,320
The more you pursue it,
the less safe you'll be.

112
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:49,040
Now we're close to the gang's boss, Mom.

113
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:52,120
Our lives won't have anything left either.

114
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:55,560
You know, they're trying
to seize our land.

115
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:58,560
The witness told the police I cheated.

116
00:19:59,360 --> 00:20:01,840
And the police believe them,
without investigating further?

117
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:10,960
Please stop. I'm scared.
Even with you being a cop,

118
00:20:11,040 --> 00:20:12,520
they're doing this.

119
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:17,600
I'm sorry. I can't stop.

120
00:20:19,640 --> 00:20:20,800
I won't back down.

121
00:20:21,880 --> 00:20:24,640
Right now, I'm under investigation
for corruption.

122
00:20:24,720 --> 00:20:26,080
I have to fight.

123
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:30,480
People need to see what I'm doing.

124
00:20:48,360 --> 00:20:50,760
I ran into someone I shouldn't have.

125
00:20:52,240 --> 00:20:53,920
A villain from the past.

126
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:58,160
Someone I trusted.

127
00:20:59,080 --> 00:21:01,160
Someone who betrayed his own team.

128
00:21:04,280 --> 00:21:08,480
He was my boss. A boss I respected.

129
00:21:09,040 --> 00:21:12,960
A boss I devoted my life to. He taught me

130
00:21:13,040 --> 00:21:15,360
to fight for justice,

131
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:19,040
to stand up for those who were oppressed,
so they wouldn't be alone.

132
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:26,560
I've faced a lot of terrible things
in my life.

133
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:28,840
But in the end,

134
00:21:30,120 --> 00:21:31,440
I haven't even been able

135
00:21:33,080 --> 00:21:34,720
to protect my family.

136
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:49,280
Rescue team, spread out! Search quickly!

137
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:54,880
Report to headquarters. We found a body.

138
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:24,160
My father, mother, and sister

139
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:29,720
were staged as suicides because of debts.

140
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:33,360
As for me,

141
00:22:34,280 --> 00:22:37,040
I was fired for crimes I never committed.

142
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:40,880
Every piece of evidence was fabricated

143
00:22:40,960 --> 00:22:43,960
to eliminate our whole team, except him.
Only he survived!

144
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:50,720
He lives comfortably atop the corpses
of our team and my family.

145
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:54,480
His name is Punlop.

146
00:23:02,280 --> 00:23:04,240
He disappeared for years.

147
00:23:04,880 --> 00:23:06,200
But today,

148
00:23:06,960 --> 00:23:09,000
he showed up at the 3C building.

149
00:23:10,320 --> 00:23:12,960
- Could it be related to Naruban?
- Someone like Punlop…

150
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:17,760
He's a cop who can be bought with money.
He might be protecting Naruban.

151
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:22,560
What about you?
Did you get anything else from Rin?

152
00:23:22,640 --> 00:23:25,840
I'm working on a way for Rin
to open Inspector Phumin's box.

153
00:23:28,160 --> 00:23:30,200
Are you sure it'll work?

154
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:34,360
You're close to Rin. You won't get killed

155
00:23:35,360 --> 00:23:37,080
or let your guard down with her, right?

156
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:11,240
What's Taiga hiding?

157
00:24:12,720 --> 00:24:14,480
There are security cameras everywhere.

158
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:17,080
Except in the bedroom and the art room.

159
00:24:17,160 --> 00:24:20,960
If you can't find anything,
pull out immediately. Don't get caught.

160
00:24:21,560 --> 00:24:22,520
Yes.

161
00:25:04,760 --> 00:25:06,360
‪It's so pretty, Sun.

162
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:07,680
Do you like it?

163
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:11,000
The most! I love everything you buy me.

164
00:25:12,120 --> 00:25:13,320
Hug me.

165
00:25:14,960 --> 00:25:16,480
Not close enough.

166
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:22,200
- Thank you.
- No problem.

167
00:25:23,280 --> 00:25:25,480
Where did you buy this outfit?

168
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:30,800
I don't remember. But you like it, right?
I'll get you another one.

169
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:33,240
I love it! The cut is perfect.

170
00:25:34,120 --> 00:25:35,480
Thank you.

171
00:25:35,560 --> 00:25:37,840
But a beautiful girl
would look good in anything.

172
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:40,320
Hey, you really have a sweet mouth.

173
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:41,440
The other side too.

174
00:26:04,480 --> 00:26:08,920
Has your hubby been spoiling you lately?
You're all smiles!

175
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:10,800
Of course!

176
00:26:10,880 --> 00:26:13,120
You've really got him well-behaved.

177
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:15,000
Pure charm, that's all.

178
00:26:16,080 --> 00:26:17,920
Always showing off
your wealth and your hubby!

179
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:20,000
Hey, Pat, this outfit is gorgeous.

180
00:26:20,080 --> 00:26:21,560
Looks familiar. Where did you get it?

181
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:23,200
- My boyfriend--
- Hey!

182
00:26:23,280 --> 00:26:25,080
- Here, this page is famous..
- <i>Hello, guys!</i>

183
00:26:25,160 --> 00:26:27,320
- Good stuff, cheap, exactly like the pics.
- <i>Aru's Back.</i>

184
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:29,280
- The seller's amazing.
- <i>This is the first dress</i>

185
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:30,680
- Let me see.
- <i>I'm going to show you.</i>

186
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:33,040
{\an8}<i>It's super cute!</i>

187
00:26:33,120 --> 00:26:35,760
{\an8}<i>If you already have a boyfriend,</i>

188
00:26:35,840 --> 00:26:38,760
{\an8}<i>wear this to dinner.</i>
<i>He'll adore you, I promise.</i>

189
00:26:38,840 --> 00:26:40,840
{\an8}And if you don't have a boyfriend yet,

190
00:26:40,920 --> 00:26:44,400
{\an8}wear this, and I guarantee you'll get one!

191
00:26:44,480 --> 00:26:46,000
{\an8}- <i>Alright then…</i>
- Here you go.

192
00:26:46,760 --> 00:26:47,600
Okay.

193
00:26:47,680 --> 00:26:49,680
Do you guys want
something to drink? My treat.

194
00:26:50,640 --> 00:26:52,320
- Sure.
- Anything's fine.

195
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:53,480
Okay.

196
00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:15,400
You disgusting, awful boyfriend!
Screw you!

197
00:27:15,920 --> 00:27:18,720
Are you seriously making me wear
your ex-wife's outfit?

198
00:27:18,800 --> 00:27:20,240
Pat, calm down!

199
00:27:20,840 --> 00:27:22,200
Get out of my house! Out!

200
00:27:22,280 --> 00:27:23,680
- Get out!
- Pat!

201
00:27:23,760 --> 00:27:25,280
Pat, listen to me.

202
00:27:25,360 --> 00:27:27,120
It's just a similar outfit, that's all.

203
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:31,680
No! You bought your ex-wife's outfit
for me to wear.

204
00:27:31,760 --> 00:27:34,200
You want her to laugh
at me behind my back, don't you?

205
00:27:34,280 --> 00:27:36,440
Now that I'm with her husband
and wearing her clothes!

206
00:27:37,080 --> 00:27:40,200
Pat, Aru was just a girlfriend.

207
00:27:40,280 --> 00:27:41,960
She's not my wife.

208
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:45,040
The only one who's my wife is you.

209
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:49,520
The only one who's my wife is you, Pat.

210
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:52,880
You haven't done anything
with that salesgirl, right?

211
00:27:54,400 --> 00:27:55,280
No.

212
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:59,120
- Swear it.
- I swear.

213
00:28:08,120 --> 00:28:10,200
You won't leave me

214
00:28:11,520 --> 00:28:13,200
like my parents left me, right?

215
00:28:18,080 --> 00:28:19,400
I won't.

216
00:28:20,480 --> 00:28:21,840
I'll stay with you.

217
00:28:46,040 --> 00:28:48,240
I thought you hated drawing already.

218
00:28:50,960 --> 00:28:52,680
I had some free time, so I tried again.

219
00:29:02,560 --> 00:29:06,640
Come on. Keep drawing. Don't stop yet.

220
00:29:15,080 --> 00:29:18,960
My wound's healed.
I won't bother you anymore.

221
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:52,240
Is this a farewell meal?

222
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:47,760
Warabi mochi, sprinkled with kinako

223
00:30:48,560 --> 00:30:50,520
and drizzled with kuromitsu.

224
00:30:56,960 --> 00:30:58,000
Enjoy.

225
00:31:09,880 --> 00:31:13,320
Ten kilos of warabi roots
yield only 70 grams of starch.

226
00:31:14,160 --> 00:31:18,400
Warabi made from real warabi starch,
not tapioca,

227
00:31:19,040 --> 00:31:21,240
is rare and expensive.

228
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:35,600
My dad and I, we love eating
warabi mochi in the summer.

229
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:31,000
Our 3C Corp. needs more investment.

230
00:32:31,880 --> 00:32:34,760
We could sell shares to outsiders.
That'll give us more capital.

231
00:32:36,200 --> 00:32:38,200
Do whatever you think is best, my friend.

232
00:32:39,680 --> 00:32:40,840
Chanchai.

233
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:43,520
Go ahead and expand the factory.

234
00:32:43,600 --> 00:32:47,280
Reach out to every country
that can help develop our technology.

235
00:32:47,360 --> 00:32:50,280
Sure. That's my specialty.

236
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:55,080
Our 3C Corp. will be number one.

237
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:06,000
Our profit this year has exceeded 200%.

238
00:33:06,080 --> 00:33:08,440
Our satellite is about to go online.

239
00:33:08,520 --> 00:33:10,320
What else are you worried about, Prin?

240
00:33:10,920 --> 00:33:12,560
Someone wants our customer data.

241
00:33:14,280 --> 00:33:15,360
Are you crazy?

242
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:18,840
Customer data is top secret.
Who would want it?

243
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:29,040
Fire Phoenix.

244
00:33:33,680 --> 00:33:37,040
I can't let my family die
the way yours did, Prin.

245
00:33:43,960 --> 00:33:46,240
{\an8}HUMAN TRAFFICKING

246
00:33:48,680 --> 00:33:50,400
Pok, Prab, Pun.

247
00:34:22,360 --> 00:34:23,920
You know this family?

248
00:34:38,480 --> 00:34:39,600
That child is me.

249
00:34:42,600 --> 00:34:44,360
I'm the only surviving child.

250
00:34:47,239 --> 00:34:50,560
I got a new life
thanks to Mr. Kenji's care.

251
00:34:56,080 --> 00:35:00,200
Rin, this box means a lot to me.

252
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:03,200
It's yours, isn't it?

253
00:35:11,160 --> 00:35:12,040
No.

254
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:15,000
My friend left it with me.

255
00:35:16,360 --> 00:35:19,520
My friend's parent is a police officer.

256
00:35:41,200 --> 00:35:45,880
{\an8}INSEETHONG FARM

257
00:35:46,840 --> 00:35:48,200
Inseethong Farm?

258
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:21,280
Two more wrong tries,
and we won't be able to open it.

259
00:36:28,920 --> 00:36:30,920
Maybe the answer's here.

260
00:37:18,680 --> 00:37:21,320
Walk carefully. Don't tear the wound.

261
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:37,240
Mr. Taiga went for inspiration?

262
00:37:38,600 --> 00:37:41,360
Yes. The team called,

263
00:37:41,440 --> 00:37:43,680
said Mr. Taiga sent word to notify us.

264
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:45,520
Rin isn't here either.

265
00:37:45,600 --> 00:37:47,960
He's probably really looking
for inspiration.

266
00:37:48,040 --> 00:37:49,680
Thailand is stunning.

267
00:37:50,280 --> 00:37:52,600
As for Rin,

268
00:37:52,680 --> 00:37:55,480
the CEO must've given her some task.

269
00:37:55,560 --> 00:37:57,440
She's been gone for several days.

270
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:03,880
I guarantee she's got
the CEO's approval for sure.

271
00:38:28,640 --> 00:38:29,600
Two rooms, please.

272
00:38:29,680 --> 00:38:31,560
Only one left.
All others are fully booked.

273
00:38:34,760 --> 00:38:35,640
Are you sure?

274
00:38:36,600 --> 00:38:37,640
Here it is.

275
00:38:43,000 --> 00:38:45,560
- Which way do we go?
- This way, please.

276
00:39:11,560 --> 00:39:14,160
I'm at Inseethong Farm.
How's everything over there?

277
00:39:14,240 --> 00:39:15,920
Madam Ratee's losing it,

278
00:39:16,000 --> 00:39:19,960
questioning me like I'm a criminal. If she
tracked you with her dad's satellite,

279
00:39:20,040 --> 00:39:21,520
<i>she'd already be on your tail.</i>

280
00:39:22,160 --> 00:39:24,080
But no rush to come back.

281
00:39:24,160 --> 00:39:28,520
<i>I've reserved everything there.</i>
<i>Only the suite is left.</i>

282
00:39:28,600 --> 00:39:32,640
Now, how you squeeze out the secret,
that's all on you.

283
00:39:46,840 --> 00:39:49,560
Rin, be careful, okay?

284
00:39:49,640 --> 00:39:52,080
Share your location with me.

285
00:39:52,160 --> 00:39:55,480
Why's your boss giving you so much work?

286
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:58,200
Heavy tasks and sending you out of town…

287
00:39:58,800 --> 00:40:02,440
They better pay you extra.
Don't just accept it.

288
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:16,000
You silly bear! What are you doing
in the bathroom so long?

289
00:40:17,320 --> 00:40:18,560
What are you doing?

290
00:40:18,640 --> 00:40:21,360
Peeking? Did you see anything?

291
00:40:22,120 --> 00:40:24,560
Or did you sneak your phone in
to film a clip to sell?

292
00:40:24,640 --> 00:40:26,440
Hey, what are you doing?

293
00:40:27,680 --> 00:40:31,400
Your creepy bear clips are lame!
Who would want to watch that stuff?

294
00:40:32,240 --> 00:40:33,520
- Wanna see?
- You silly!

295
00:40:33,600 --> 00:40:35,680
Hey, just a peek. Come on.

296
00:40:35,760 --> 00:40:37,160
- Just a peek first.
- Use the bathroom quickly!

297
00:40:37,240 --> 00:40:40,160
- I'm next! Hurry up!
- Check it out. Maybe I can sell it, madam.

298
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:23,280
Come here. I'll help.

299
00:41:24,760 --> 00:41:25,800
It's done.

300
00:41:25,880 --> 00:41:27,480
If it gets infected, it'll be trouble.

301
00:41:27,560 --> 00:41:29,160
The hospital can handle it.

302
00:42:09,840 --> 00:42:13,640
I'll buy it, all of 3C's stuff!

303
00:42:13,720 --> 00:42:17,280
I'll kick Nunnapat out.
Wherever she goes to work,

304
00:42:17,360 --> 00:42:20,600
I'll push her out, kick her out,
and buy everything up.

305
00:42:30,960 --> 00:42:31,960
I'll pour it for you.

306
00:42:35,880 --> 00:42:37,080
Thanks.

307
00:42:45,560 --> 00:42:47,080
Does it make you happy?

308
00:42:47,600 --> 00:42:50,160
Of course! Haven't you ever held a grudge?

309
00:42:52,720 --> 00:42:53,840
I have.

310
00:42:55,480 --> 00:42:57,200
My grudge was so strong, I wanted to kill.

311
00:42:59,080 --> 00:43:03,680
But then I calmed down and laughed
at myself for thinking such stupid things.

312
00:43:10,600 --> 00:43:12,520
Stop pretending to be good.

313
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:17,720
I'm just a normal person,

314
00:43:18,560 --> 00:43:20,080
not good or anything.

315
00:43:21,160 --> 00:43:23,960
I just know what my flaws are,

316
00:43:24,520 --> 00:43:27,440
and I try not to trigger
the worst in myself.

317
00:43:39,600 --> 00:43:40,920
I don't want to be so bad,

318
00:43:42,320 --> 00:43:43,480
to the point

319
00:43:45,320 --> 00:43:46,840
that there's no turning back.

320
00:43:49,000 --> 00:43:50,560
If it's necessary,

321
00:43:51,680 --> 00:43:52,840
do it.

322
00:43:53,640 --> 00:43:54,880
Go all the way.

323
00:43:55,640 --> 00:43:58,080
Don't look back, and don't regret it.

324
00:44:00,480 --> 00:44:01,720
Every one of us

325
00:44:02,640 --> 00:44:05,440
can close their eyes and shut our minds.

326
00:44:07,320 --> 00:44:08,520
But right here…

327
00:44:10,200 --> 00:44:11,440
Inside here…

328
00:44:12,800 --> 00:44:14,320
Every feeling…

329
00:44:16,400 --> 00:44:17,960
No one sees it.

330
00:44:19,080 --> 00:44:20,440
But you always know…

331
00:44:24,120 --> 00:44:25,360
what you're feeling

332
00:44:27,160 --> 00:44:28,600
inside.

333
00:44:31,160 --> 00:44:32,200
Don't!

334
00:44:33,680 --> 00:44:37,320
I order you.
You're not allowed to feel anything.

335
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:40,720
Don't.

336
00:44:43,440 --> 00:44:44,520
Don't.

337
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:05,720
{\an8}Did your father ever tell you
about the cases,

338
00:45:05,800 --> 00:45:08,720
{\an8}like the family
that was murdered ten years ago?

339
00:45:13,040 --> 00:45:15,400
{\an8}Taiga, Mr. Naruban was poisoned.

340
00:45:16,320 --> 00:45:18,000
{\an8}You've been through a lot, Naruban.

341
00:45:18,080 --> 00:45:19,680
{\an8}Soon you'll be off duty.

342
00:45:19,760 --> 00:45:21,240
{\an8}You'll finally get a long rest.

343
00:45:51,760 --> 00:45:55,920
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn

